tourBios.curYrHigh: Finished the Web.com Tour season with 24 starts, one runner-up, one third-place finish, three top-10s and 11 cuts made. Was 60th on the combined final money list...Season began with three missed cuts before he claimed his first career top-10 performance on Tour at the Brasil Champions in March. Twin 64s on Friday and Saturday moved him into a first-place tie with eventual champion Peter Malnati after 54 holes. Watched as Malnati pulled away but birdied two of the final three holes on Sunday for a 1-under 70 and a T2 with six others...Next 10 starts saw him make four cuts, with his top finish a T48 in Mexico...Recorded top 10s at the Stonebrae Classic (T6) and Digital Ally Open (T3), which placed him 41st on the money list. Was one shot off the lead after opening the Digital Ally event near Kansas City with a pair of 64s. Closed 69-67...Shot nines of 29 twice, in Brazil and again in Dallas...Would miss his last two cuts to finish the Regular Season 52nd in earnings...In the Web.com Tour Finals, made the last three of four cuts, posting T62, T56 and T43 finishes.

tourBios.carHigh: 2014: Finished T16 at Web.com Tour Q-School...Played in 13 PGA Tour Latinoamerica events, made 10 cuts and posted one top-10, at the Lexus Panama Classic (T6). Was 43rd on the final order of merit...In five Web.com Tour appearances, made three cuts, with his best finish a T17 at the News Sentinel Open in August.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Was Indiana Amateur champion in 2011, second-team All Big-10 in 2012 and an Academic All-American in 2011 and 2012...Was IHSAA state high school champion in 2007.
tourBios.personal: Attended Columbus North High School...Earliest golf memory was riding in a cart with grandparents with a 3-wood, 8-iron and putter...Favorite TV shows are "Blacklist," "Suits" and "Prison Break."...Favorite pro teams are the Indianapolis Colts, Denver Broncos and Indiana Pacers...Favorite music group is Florida Georgia Line...Would like to trade places with Tiger Woods to know what it feels like to be the best in the world...Met Woods at Isleworth G&CC...Best concert attended was Luke Bryan at Purdue University...Dream foursome would be Woods, his grandpa and Bobby Knight...Uncle, Andrew Johnson, won on the Web.com Tour in 2005...Twitter handle is @trduncan1.
